data.name: ClientBumped_MBMessage
data.value:
Your connection to the StackHash Service was bumped on {0} at {1}.
A connection may be bumped because you have not used StackHash for a while and another client connected to the Service. You may also have been bumped by a client running on the same computer as the StackHash Service.
StackHash will attempt to connect to the Service again when you click OK.
data.comment: Parameters are the date and time of the bump.

data.name: LicenseEventLimitHit_MBMessage
data.value:
You have exceeded the number of events that StackHash is licensed for. Synchronization will not add new events.
The licensed number of events applies to products that are enabled for synchronization. You may be able to disable older products in order to reduce the number of consumed events.
Alternatively you can upgrade your license to allow StackHash to store more events.
